OL,3,CGovernment ups subsidies for GP
OL,4,Cappointments by #10 in Jersey
OL,6,FHowever, Jersey's Social Security
OL,7,FMinister, Deputy Lyndsay Feltham, says
OL,8,Fsurgeries are "contractually obliged"
OL,9,Fto reduce their fees from the current
OL,10,Flevels.
OL,12,FShe adds: "I don't expect them to be
OL,13,Fincreasing their fees in order to
OL,14,Fcompensate for this additional
OL,15,Fincrease in our subsidy.
OL,17,F"I am confident that GPs also want to
OL,18,Fmake their services affordable for
OL,19,Fpeople."
